import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Penicillin', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['Penicillin'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['Penicillin'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of Penicillin?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Neomycin', kde=True, color='blue', bins=20)
    median_neomycin = data['Neomycin'].median()
    plt.axvline(median_neomycin, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {median_neomycin:.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Neomycin?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='Penicillin', y='Streptomycin', hue='Gram_Staining')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between Penicillin and Streptomycin?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Gram Staining')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    gram_staining_counts = data['Gram_Staining'].value_counts()
    ax = sns.barplot(x=gram_staining_counts.index, y=gram_staining_counts.values)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of Gram_Staining?", wrap=True)
    ax.set_xlabel("Gram_Staining")
    ax.set_ylabel("Frequency")
    ax.legend(gram_staining_counts.index, title="Gram_Staining")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
